Stuarts idea of having the syntax of:

network 128.102.1.0	255.255.255.0
network 192.35.86.0	255.255.255.0

is a much better syntax than what I previously suggested (which was
having a subnet mask which was applied to all hosts). In fact, since
the time I wrote the note I have discovered that we may have a class B
and a class C network on our crays with each network having a different
subnet mask. Stuart's idea would facilitate and even broader sorting
capability.

rich

